SIMPLE: steeple-crowned
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Steeple-crowned
<hw>Stee"ple-crowned`</hw> <pr>(-kround`)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Bearing a steeple; <as>as, a <ex>steeple-crowned</ex>
building</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having a crown shaped like a steeple; <as>as, a
<ex>steeple-crowned</ex> hat</as>; also, wearing a hat with such a
crown.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This grave, bearded, sable-cloaked, and <qex>steeple-crowned</qex>
progenitor.</q> <rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Steepled</ent>⟦br⟧
